// @check
// @error-at 8:9 Type `D` is defined in terms of itself with no base type, so it can never have a value
// An UNUSED self-cyclic alias still flags. Type aliases resolve lazily (on use),
// so the use-site self-cycle check in `getConcreteType` never fires when the
// alias is never referenced — which left a bare `type D = D` silently accepted
// (PR #189 review: "I don't see an lsp error for `type D = D`?"). The parser now
// reports the degenerate self-cycle at the declaration itself, so it surfaces in
// `vl check` / the LSP regardless of whether `D` is ever used.
type D = D
